  , issueCommentBody =
      "+1 for me too. The major thing about using arrays instead of tables is atomicity/race conditions. For example:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndoc.update(function(doc) {\r\n    return doc.merge({\r\n        array_key: doc('array_key').append({\r\n            parent: doc('array_key').nth(-1)('id')\r\n        })\r\n    })\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nUsing the array here, I know that the `nth(-1)('id')` will never be the same between queries. Not sure how I could work around this with the table approach."
